sentences: Gastón Guzmán Muñoz (c. 1937 - August 28, 2019) was a Chilean singer-songwriter.
A native of Angol, Chile, he was a founder, with his brother Eduardo (1940-2012), of the Chilean musical group, Quelentaro.
In 2015, he was honored with the designation as a fundamental figure of Chilean music.
